title: The Cube PARKOUR ? Bedrock
briefDescription: A challenging, multiplayer OR single-player, PARKOUR map made for Bedrock with 24 increasingly difficult levels! The map also uses our own custom texture pack! Can you ...

crawledImageUrls.text:
A challenging, multiplayer OR single-player, PARKOUR map made for Bedrock with 24 increasingly difficult levels! The map also uses our own custom texture pack! Can you reach the top of The Cube?
The Cube Parkour map has very simplistic and clean levels designed to test players? skills and challenge even the best parkour masters!

There are 8 parkour stages per floor of The Cube, the very beginning is setup for low level players; jumping further through each floor, you?ll come across increasingly difficult stages.
Any player can make as much progress towards the end as they can, and as fast as they can! Allowing for an intense race to reach the end if playing with friends!

A advanced Parkour map that is playable with 30 players , without any pack to download and without any lag possible . We added custom death messages , deaths counter and you don?t have to click re-spawn button because you re-spawn automatically .
What is this ?

This is a ultimate multiplayer map made for parkour with smart system boosted by BOT12
How to play ?

The game is playable SinglePlayer and Multiplayer , You can play with all your friends with doing /setmaxplayers 30 .
Once you?re ready to play open the chest and move the item to any direction and you will get teleported to the begging of the map .
You will have a jump boost item every 30 seconds to use it you need to drop it and it will effect all players that in 2*3*3 area by Jump boost III for 5 seconds .
When you fall (miss a jump) You won?t lose any booster but you will get teleported automatically to the last checkpoint .
You need to finish the map first without dying 50 times .
The map is on difficulty normal from the beginning to the end .
Is it limit play ?

Well It?s unlimited for playing .
Can i use a texture pack ?

Yes You can use any texture pack that doesn?t change the sounds .

title: Cloud City ? Parkour Adventure
briefDescription: Amazing Cloud City from the Star Wars saga is already in minecraft! Discover this amazing place and save it from the Empire.Cloud City is ...

crawledImageUrls.text:
Amazing Cloud City from the Star Wars saga is already in minecraft! Discover this amazing place and save it from the Empire.
Cloud City is one of the largest and strongest buildings in the world of Star Wars. It is here that Luke Skywalker meets his father and Han Solo is frozen.
Take on the role of Lando Calrissian and save this city from destruction by the Minecraft empire! Reach this place with parkour and save this place! Watch out for huge heights and huge clouds under Cloud City!
I saw ? I saw a city in the clouds.? To reach the city you have to overcome difficult parkour that hangs high above the surface of the square ground.
The city is big, explore it and discover its nooks and crannies. Be careful not to fall off these huge skyscrapers.
Defeat parkour and save Cloud City from destruction by the Empire! Watch out, evil powers are waiting for you and they can kill you.

title: 5?5 Parkour (NEW FEATURES)
briefDescription: What happens when you only have a 5x5 area of space? You go up! 5x5 Parkour has little segments of parkour for you to finish! ...

crawledImageUrls.text:
What happens when you only have a 5?5 area of space? You go up! 5?5 Parkour has little segments of parkour for you to finish! The higher you go, the harder it gets, but there are checkpoints that makes the parkour a little less frustrating.
In 5?5 parkour, there are coloured segments for you to pass, with each segment you pass, it gets harder and harder. There are a total of 9 segments. The segments get high so watch your step to not fall down!
NEW ADDED FEATURES:
? The ?Un-Alive? Machine 9000.
? Togglable Features
Togglable Features include Friendly Fire/PvP, Fall Damage, and Invisibility.
Friendly Fire/PvP is pretty self-explanatory along with all the other features. It toggles the ability to hit others. This can be used to do sabatoge others in a competition!
Fall Damage toggles the ability to be damaged or hurt when falling. This can be used to have a quick way of respawning from a high height instead of using The ?Un-Alive? Machine 9000.
Invisibility toggles the ability to be turned invisible. This is used when there are too many people to see the parkour. You will still be see others because everyone will be equiped with leather boots.

title: Der Grobe Krieg ? Zombie Parkour!
briefDescription: Der Grobe Krieg is a parkour map with a style of combat. throughout the map are places where you can sell rotten flesh and trade ...

crawledImageUrls.text:
Der Grobe Krieg is a parkour map with a style of combat. throughout the map are places where you can sell rotten flesh and trade them in for weapons the end goal is to defeat the boss and win the map! This is re-playable and supports multiplayer! Also See if you can find the hidden barrier blocks(they make life easier)!
Der Grobe Krieg (translates to The Great War) Is based on the battlefields of world war 1! Someone or something has poisoned the area we/I(the player or players) must escape. everyone has changed?
They are living dead? In this map you do a world war 1 themed parkour throughout the map zombies will spawn as they try to stop you getting to the end when you kill a zombie you will receive rotten flesh which you can sell for points these can then be spent at checkpoints throughout the map. Also at these checkpoints you can buy items with points. There are a total of 3 checkpoints throughout the map however there are more re-spawn points.
There are special blocks throughout the map these are black and green blocks green will give you poison and black will give you wither effect. Also there is hidden barrier blocks they are secret and make the map easier so good luck finding them. You can play this map solo or multiplayer(as many people as you want). The boss battle at the end is 2 waves of different mobs it is hard however you re-spawn in the boss arena when you die! I Plan to make a sequel to this map even though this was a small project.
This is my first public bedrock map and hope you enjoy if you have any bugs let me know and i will happily take any feedback and suggestions for the map.
